{
  "stem": "17761.4",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 120.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And they were mostly involved in constructing bridges, railways, rail stations, highways, repairing highways, and so on.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "The majority of the time, I worked at the construction of two bridges over the Dniester, because when the Russians withdrew, they destroyed the bridges.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "So they-- I don't even know where exactly those two are the same places.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But there were no bridges.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "We had to go over by boat, because there are no bridges that you could over.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So one bridge was for railways.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the other bridge was for-- for the highway.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That means for cars, for for tanks, and so on.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we worked very hard to build up these bridges.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I know that one of the bridges had 14 pillars, because the Dniester was wider-- between a kilometer and a kilometer and a half.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It's close to a mile, the bridge of Dniester.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So some people worked on that side of the Dniester.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Some others were shipped over with little boats to the other side of the Dniester.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was very often among those who were shipped out.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It is a funny little story.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was a German soldier who was usually responsible for shipping us over.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was always some soldiers with guns there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And as we started to go on the river, he used to say, [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH].",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Sing the-- the Jewish song.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we sang-- we sang the HaTikvah.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was surrealistic to see those deportees, those Jews there in that situation, and the German soldiers, and he's happy that the Jews are singing HaTikvah.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was many times it happened to us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And there I worked almost until the end of the-- of the German occupation.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But there were a number of centers.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We called them [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
